CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 15, 1959, pg. A1, reads: "Filth and Stench Found in 3rd Ward - Unreliable - Some irresponsible person left this rubbish on the already offensive lot in 1500 block of Clark St., where a city dumpster sets on a sea of insect breeding garbage, thrown there by other careless residents. The city health inspectors have not taken stringent measures to clean up the area. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Pile of debris including dark sofa, light colored armchair, mattress with box spring, bushel basket, and other furniture and refuse, dumped in front of brick wall, on 1500 block of Clark Street, Hill District
